snippet.textDisplay: Some of the symbolism in the video reminded me of the video for The Hills Have Eyes. Particularly, in the scenes where the people were holding onto him to prevent his spirit from leaving this world. There was a similar event in the music video for The Hills Have Eyes where people were holding onto him as he was walking away from the car. What the people were holding onto in actuality was his soul, and when the car blew up, he died, and that's why they let go of him and started crying.

snippet.textDisplay:
So all our theories came close but were incorrect (mine included). In the Variety interview he explains it all:


INTERVIEWER: People spend their entire lives running from demons — not many want to go back.

ABEL TESFAYE: I didn’t want to, it was like, “This is who I am.” Sometimes you try to run away from who you are, and you always get back to that place. And by the time you get to the end of this album you realize I’m not that person. I was, but now I’m growing and older and wiser and I’m gonna have children some time, and I’m going to tell them that “You don’t have to be that person.” I really wanted you to feel uncomfortable when you heard it, I really wanted to get inside the head of the person who hates himself and hates life and hates the person who made him that way.

Link to the interview - https://variety.com/2020/music/news/the-weeknd-after-hours-track-by-track-1234574136/

snippet.textDisplay: An interpretation: After the “In Your Eyes” music video where his head is cut off, this is his transcendence to Heaven after Las Vegas. The films begins with a flash of light & memories (symbolizing entering a flashback). Here he is, in his House of Balloons: Surrounded by women, parties, drinks & alcohol. It’s a painful storm of celebration as he suffers. Through it all, he keeps seeing this one woman, likely someone he used to be in love with & who’s heartbreak tormented him through it all. They were his escape from her, but he could never move past her memory. He continues to suffer as the drugs & tormenting memories wreak havoc on his life. Finally, he bleeds out. At 2:10, they carry his dead body away. After that, his fans (or past memories) are fight ferociously to keep his soul for themselves, until finally, he finds peace and walks towards the light at 2:38.
